headline: Paramount Skydance Stock Plunges After Big Gains. Here’s Why.
summary: Paramount Skydance  stock was tumbling on Thursday, putting it on course to give up some of its eye-popping gains from the previous two sessions.  Shares, trading under the new ticker PSKY, dropped 6.3% to $14.02 in early trading.  The shares notched their best two-day stretch since Paramount listed via an initial public offering in 1990, through Wednesday.
